          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-05-30 18:59:03" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of χεῖλος ‘lip,’ not occurring in the NT, except as a metonymy for speech; see χεῖλος[b] {D:33.74}) the strip of land close to a body of water</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>shore</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In the NT contexts in which {L:παράλιος&lt;SDBG:παράλιος:000000&gt;} ({D:1.61}), χεῖλος, and {L:αἰγιαλός&lt;SDBG:αἰγιαλός:000000&gt;} ({D:1.63}) occur, it is possible to say that χεῖλος ‘shore’ probably involves a somewhat narrower strip of land than {L:παράλιος&lt;SDBG:παράλιος:000000&gt;} ‘a coastal region,’ but χεῖλος evidently denotes a somewhat wider area than {L:αἰγιαλός&lt;SDBG:αἰγιαλός:000000&gt;} ‘beach, shore.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
